page_id: S4-X-02
title: Platform capabilities
platform: Linux
repository: Not connected
sections:
  - Capability matrix
  - Binding contract
  - Supported APIs
  - Type mappings
  - Limited or missing capabilities
actions:
  open_repository_settings: PlatformDifferencesView.OpenRepositorySettingsAsync
  export_diagnostics: disabled - Diagnostics are not available on this platform yet.
  check_capabilities: PlatformDifferencesView.CheckCapabilitiesAsync
  check_contract: PlatformDifferencesView.CheckContractAsync
  close: PlatformDifferencesView.Close
safety:
  - The page has Open repository settings, Export diagnostics, and Close footer actions.
  - Diagnostics are disabled when no platform diagnostics service is wired, so no blank package is generated.
  - The page calls get_platform_capabilities through PlatformDifferencesCoreBridge for C4-17 rows.
  - The page calls inspect_binding_contract through PlatformDifferencesCoreBridge.
  - The page passes target platform and binding version only; it does not read a repository path.
  - The page does not call watcher health, import, rescan, sync, or Trash APIs.
  - The check is read-only and does not open, move, delete, rename, or modify repository files.
states:
  checking_capabilities: Checking platform capabilities...
  loading: Checking binding contract...
  loaded: Binding contract is available.
  failed: Binding contract unavailable.
  capability_failed: Capability snapshot unavailable; rows fall back to Unknown.
